COMMENT ON COLUMN dbo."Incident"."Incident_Cost" IS 'The value of any quantifiable monetary loss directly resulting from the incident. Examples include the value of repairs necessitated by vandalism of a school facility, the value of personnel resources used for repairs or consumed by the incident, the value of stolen items, and the value of time consumed by an incident (e.g., instructional time involved in evacuating a school during a false fire alarm).  Cost may be reported by specific monetary amount or range. [CEDS Element: Incident Cost, ID:000505]';

